reviewText: A lighthearted comedy that almost gets too serious, but enjoyable all the way through, with an ending that makes everything all worthwhile! Lacey Chabert hands in a terrific job of acting, where you might just believe she IS her character who can't find that right man.Although not a main character, SNL's Chris Kattan is always good for comic relief, too!Because of subject content and language, I would recommend SSILA for 18 and over.

reviewText: I wasn't quite sure what to expect in this movie and to be honest I mainly watched it because Lacy Chabert was in it so I figured it wouldn't be too bad. Truthfully it was actually pretty good and it's about people looking for love and often overlooking what's right in front of them! I would describe it as a nice feel good romcom and yes, horror movies aside I;m a sucker for a good romantic comedy, it's a character flaw! This is without a doubt a chick flick but guys if you're looking to score points with your significant other than you could do worse!
